They bonded and Hulk cared for him, but the kitten has panleukopenia that we didn't know about. Though he had the vaccine against the virus, Hulk became sick. The doctor misdiagnosed him because he tested negative, and he was in the vet clinic for 5 days without specific treatment and then out of nowhere the doctor said he will die if not taken to the ER for better specialists. For 5 days the vet mislead us that everything will be fine. The lack of proper treatment at the vet clinic put Hulk into liver failure. From the medical chart we saw he wasn't given any nutrition or vitamins through IV, so Hulk being unable to hold any food in was starved for 5 days, his body started eating itself and he developed fatty liver which caused liver failure. We took him and the kitten to the ER, and a couple of thousands later, it seems like the kitten will make it but Hulk needs extensive care for a chance to survive and the hospital  bill is $1200 a day.  I can no longer afford it but also cannot bare the thought of euthanizing him. I cannot stand the thought of him dying with his last memories being locked in a hospital cage after being left to die and starved by the vet. We took him at the early stages so his chances of survival should have been over 90%. If we can come together to raise funds for 3-4 more days in the hospital it would give Hulk a chance to survive.  Hulk only has until Thursday august 30th in the afternoon for funds to be raised.ï»¿
